<event name="SLAVER_LANIUS_SLAVE" unique="true">
	<text>You enter a beacon located in a very desolate system, used only as an intermediate waypoint to span the gap between more important systems for FTL travel. There is little here other than a lone civilian station above the beacon. Quite awhile after arriving at the beacon, you are hailed by a black ship sporting black and red paint docked at the station.</text>
	<choice>
		<text>Continue.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The ship's captain coughs, then speaks, "We have obtained a miraculous metal man, capable of not only living without oxygen, but actively making the air unbreathable. However, our ship's life support system can't sustain its incredible qualities for more than a short span of time, so we're stuck here at this station in this miserable system. Agree to buy our metal man and we'll give you the deal of a lifetime."</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_SLAVER_ALL" hostile="false"/> 
			<choice>
				<text>Purchase the Lanius.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The slaver is delighted to be freed of their liability and still earn a profit. They waste no time to transfer over the Lanius.</text>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-30" max="-30"/>
