					<crewMember amount="1" class="lanius">Laythe</crewMember>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Slavery is deplorable. Fight the slaver.</text>
				<event>
					<text>As you engage, the ship quickly undocks from the station and prepares to fight back.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/> 
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Ignore the ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You put some distance between you and the slaver. Once you're sure they won't bother you anymore, you consider doing something aboard the ship.</text>
					<choice>
						<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
						<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
					<choice>
						<text>Do nothing.</text>
						<event/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="mind" hidden="true">
				<text>(Mind control) Convince them to donate the Lanius.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Your mind control system is able to easily convince the slaver captain that she should give you the Lanius for free so that they may depart for a more profitable beacon. The Lanius is quickly ejected towards your ship in a small shuttle before the effects of the mind control wear off. Realizing they've been tricked, the slaver separates from the station and powers up its weapons.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="lanius">Laythe</crewMember>
					<ship hostile="true"/> 
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

