<event name="QUEST_SMUGGLER_RAID_START" unique="true">
	<text>You notice some traffic around a smuggler station orbiting a moon close by. You tune into their comms and hear an offer for a mercenary job.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_GENERIC" hostile="false"/> 
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ask for more details.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A grizzly looking smuggler answers your hail. "Lookin' for a job? Well I got one for you, if you ain't a coward. A rather... expensive and pretty illegal shipment of mine was confiscated by those stuck up Zoltan assholes, saying all of their usual crap. Thing is, this is OUR sector, not theirs. I want that shipment back, and I don't care how so long as it's unharmed. You up for the challenge?"</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Accept.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Well that's a surprise. Alright kid, I'll transfer over the co-ordinates. Find the depot and kill the guard. Go to the storage room and there'll be a vault. Ain't no way they opened it yet, only I got the passcode, and the vault's super blast resistant. I have no choice but to trust you, so here you go. The code is 7-E-Blue. Don't ask why. Get the cargo and there will be another list of coordinates to bring it back to. I'll be waiting for you there."</text>
					<quest event="QUEST_SMUGGLER_RAID"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Refuse.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Pffft, figured. Ain't like I want some idiot Fed hauling around my valuables anyways." He ends the call abruptly.</text>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the station.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You aren't about to go selling yourself as mercenaries. You have standards.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
